article.headline: Louisiana-Monroe 61, South Alabama 58
article.story: MONROE, La. -- Dynile Forbes scored 14 points and Louisiana-Monroe defeated South Alabama 61-58 on Thursday night. The Warhawks (7-11, 2-5 Sun Belt Conference) trailed 58-57 with 1:59 remaining, before hitting four free throws and getting three defensive stops. Tommie Sykes gave ULM the lead for good, at 59-58, on two free throws with 1:37 to go, and Forbes hit two more with 15 seconds left. The Warhawks were outrebounded 40-29 and shot just 30 percent from the field (15 of 50). However, they shot 80 percent from the free throw line (24 of 30) and snapped a two-game losing streak and seven-game skid to the Jaguars (11-7, 3-3). South Alabama led 18-14 and it stayed close throughout most of the first half. But a 13-3 run gave ULM a 27-21 lead with 5 minutes left, en route to a 31-25 halftime lead. Martino Brock scored 13 points and grabbed 12 rebounds for the Jaguars.
